Text:
Dammit... Those Tuna King turds should stay open
later... I missed out on getting a nice tuna burger
again today...

Ah, whatever, this is the last round, anyway... We
got a good amount of stuff, so the time's almost
here... Hee-hee!
The time's almost here for what, exactly?
What?! Is someone there?

By "good amount of stuff," are you referring to the
documents in the basement?
Who the hell are you?!

Um, I think it goes...we have no names to waste on
the likes of you!

Even after spreading all those rumors, there's still
dunces trying to get in here... Die!

Heh... You think you can hurt us with such shoddy
swordsmanship?
Wh-What?! B-But you're just a girl!

Now, accept this fight and tell us everything!
Fail to do so, and you'll taste my blade!
Stooooop! That's enough!
Hey! Why are you stopping me?!

Because we'll never learn the truth if you slip up
and kill him, duh!
I'd never slip up and kill someone!

Uh...you might think that, but there's no telling
with you when things get real, Gammy!

Aha! You just said something mean, didn't you! Do
you really think I'm so incompetent?!
Eeep!

You hold the key to the mystery here. I want you to
tell us everything, and leave nothing out, are we
clear?
Yikes...! F-Fine... J-Just don't kill me!
Who are you?
J-Just an...o-ordinary citizen, n-no one specialâ€”

We found your Cult robes. So this will go better for
you if you dispense with the petty lies.
What...?!
How... How do you know about the Cult?!
We're the ones asking the questions.
Eeep...!
Where did you get this list of names?
O-Oh, the list...!
It's...a secret document of the Cult.

And why would a lowly member such as yourself have
access to such a thing?
U-Uh, well, you see...

If you're having trouble understanding the question,
perhaps I can start by helping your hearing.
O-Okay, okay, I get it... Just stop, please!
I...took it! I stole it!
You stole it?!
Was it that easy to steal?
S-So..normally I guard the Cult's archivesâ€”

And you stole this on the job while no one was
watching.
Why did you hide what you stole in this manor house?

W-Well, because word gets around in the trade city!
No one comes around this place at least on account of
all the trouble...!

The guild's got it on lockdown, there's the ghost...
Yeah, nothing's gone right here, because of the
haunting!

No one noticed what you took was gone? Even if they
didn't know who did it, the stuff'd still be missing.

N-No... The archives only get inventoried every two
years, and we relocate them, too!

As long as I made my escape before then...I'd have
nothin' to worry about, see?

Two years?! That lines up with when all the haunting
stuff started.
That's why today's the last day... Heheheh...hahaha!
Why are you laughing?!

Ahahahahaha! Thanks for the extra time, ladies!
You shouldn't have been so chatty!

If you knew about the ghost, you should've been on
guard against me summoning it!

Now this here, is a spirit used by those creeps from
Orum to take out heretics!

I've almost got everything going my way, so no way
am I letting a few kids stop me!

I'm gonna sell that list for a ton of cash and then
party the rest of my life away!

You're going to sell it? What about your loyalty to
the Cult?!

As if I have any! Who wants to spend forever toiling
at the very bottom for scraps?

A rank-and-file cultist, not skilled enough to be
made into one of the Children, and too lowly to even
know who we areâ€”

And an organization so bloated it fails to notice the
decay and corruption at its extremities.
What's so funny?!
Nothing. I simply find it laughable.

Now, let's get this battle underway. We have the
information we need.
Allow me to dispose of the ghost!

And once that's done, shall we send him to the bottom
of the sea?

Yes, by all means. Just make sure to get the location
of the archives out of him before you do.

In the meantime, I'll deal with the minor spirits the
ghost calls forth.

What?! I dunno who the hell you girls are, but don't
think you've got me beat!
